0vw, 300px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/ikoula.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/ikoula-150x150.png.webp 150w\" data-was-processed=\"true\"><br>\nHave you used a <a href=\"https://www.synology.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"synology\">Synology</a> NAS at home? Do you want one in the cloud?</p><p>For those unfamiliar, Synology makes a line of inexpensive NAS systems aimed at both the home and small business markets.&nbsp; They have very attractive web-based interfaces with a neat desktop-like graphical interface and they\u2019re very easy to use.&nbsp; One of the key attractions is that you can leave them running all the time with minimal power, as opposed to running a full-bore homemade x86 tower with something like <a href=\"https://www.freenas.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"FreeNAS\">FreeNAS</a>.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.ikoula.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"iKoula\">iKoula</a> offers hosted Synology systems.&nbsp; For example, you can get a <strong>2TB SATA for \u20ac10.49/month</strong>.</p><p>Part of the attraction is the Synology all-in-one interface, which allows you to effortlessly turn on and off services, mange users, and configure features without having to edit text files or learn Linux system administration.&nbsp; Diehard Unix neckbeards can find cheaper (and more performant) offers but you are unlikely to find any that are more user-friendly.</p><p>For more information, check out <a href=\"https://www.ikoula.com/en/dedicated-server#synology\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" aria-label=\"iKoula\">iKoula\u2019s web site</a>.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/synology_nas.png\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-27967 litespeed-loaded\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/synology_